<header class="header">
  <h1>Best Greenhouse Repair Tape for Torn Plastic</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    A small tear can turn into a major problem quickly if the repair doesn’t hold.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most greenhouse repairs, the best tape is a UV-resistant patch tape designed for polyethylene film that bonds strongly and stays flexible over time.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Greenhouse plastic expands, contracts, and flexes with temperature changes. Any repair needs to move with it while staying firmly attached.
  </p>
  <p>
    The wrong tape may stick initially but fail after a few days of sun and weather exposure.
  </p>
</header>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Quick Answer: What Works Best?</h2>

  <div class="quickAnswerBox">
    <ul class="plainList">
      <li><strong>Best overall:</strong> UV-resistant greenhouse patch tape.</li>
      <li><strong>Best durability:</strong> thick, flexible adhesive-backed tape.</li>
      <li><strong>Best repair method:</strong> apply on both sides when possible.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p>
    Adhesion and UV resistance are the most important factors.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Why Regular Tape Fails on Greenhouse Plastic</h2>

  <p>
    Standard tapes are not designed for outdoor exposure or for bonding to polyethylene film. Sunlight breaks down adhesives, and temperature changes cause peeling.
  </p>

  <p>
    Greenhouse-specific tape is formulated to handle these conditions.
  </p>

  <p>
    This is why purpose-built repair tape performs much better over time.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Makes a Good Repair Tape</h2>

  <h3>Strong Adhesion to Poly Film</h3>
  <p>
    The tape must bond securely to smooth plastic surfaces.
  </p>

  <h3>UV Resistance</h3>
  <p>
    Prevents breakdown from prolonged sun exposure.
  </p>

  <h3>Flexibility</h3>
  <p>
    Allows the repair to move with the plastic as it expands and contracts.
  </p>

  <h3>Thickness and Strength</h3>
  <p>
    Provides structural support across the tear.
  </p>
</section>

